article.headline: Canisius 88, Fairfield 60
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Frank Turner scored a season-high 26 points and Jovan Robinson added 16 points and six rebounds as Canisius beat Fairfield 88-60 Friday night in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference. Turner went 7-of-11 from the field and 9-of-12 from the foul line as Canisius (4-17, 2-9 MAAC) handed the Stags their most lopsided loss since dropping an 85-60 decision at Wake Forest. Greg Logins scored 14 points with 8 boards for the Golden Griffins. Elton Frazier had 12 points and Bob Bevilaqua 11. Fairfield (7-14, 5-6) shot just 33.3 percent for the game, connecting on 16-of-48 from them floor. Jonathan Han led the Stags with 14 points and 5 assists, while Mike Evanovich scored 11. Canisius, which led 53-26 at halftime, shot 29-of-47 from the floor for the game (61.7 percent), converting 14-of-23 3-pointers and 14-for-23 from the foul line.
